<section class="pres-digital-strategy" id="pres-digital-strategy">
  <div class="pres-digital-strategy__content">
    <h2 class="pres-digital-strategy__heading">Digital land. Held like gold.</h2>
    <p class="pres-digital-strategy__subtitle">
      We buy and hold Bitcoin as a long-term store of value.
    </p>

    <ul class="pres-digital-strategy__benefits">
      <li class="pres-digital-strategy__benefit">
        <span class="pres-digital-strategy__benefit-title">Scarce, like our coastal land</span>
        <span class="pres-digital-strategy__benefit-desc">
          Bitcoin has a hard supply cap. 21 million units, and no central bank can print more.
        </span>
      </li>
      <li class="pres-digital-strategy__benefit">
        <span class="pres-digital-strategy__benefit-title">Held long-term, like gold</span>
        <span class="pres-digital-strategy__benefit-desc">
          Custodied at BitGo, a federally chartered U.S. bank. $250M insured by Lloyd's. We don't
          trade it.
        </span>
      </li>
      <li class="pres-digital-strategy__benefit">
        <span class="pres-digital-strategy__benefit-title">Wall Street holds them too</span>
        <span class="pres-digital-strategy__benefit-desc">
          BlackRock, Fidelity, BNY Mellon, Bank of America, even the U.S. Government. Now a mature
          asset class.
        </span>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="pres-digital-strategy__source">
      Sources: BitGo (OCC national trust bank) &middot; Lloyd's of London &middot; public filings of BlackRock,
      Fidelity, BNY Mellon, Bank of America
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

